    feat: implement core storage transaction support + in-memory implementation (#1674) ## Description Breakout from the larger PR #1673 ## Changes **Note:** This PR _only_ affects test-related code. The new transactions are _not used_ in any actual tests here (see the other PR for that), with the exception of the handful of new tests explicitly testing the transactional functionality for the in-mem store. Highlights: - `SharedStore` now implements `Transactable` which lets you call `begin_transaction()` to get an `InMemoryTransaction` handle, which you can `commit()` or `rollback()`. - `DbRead` is implemented for both `SharedStore` and `InMemoryTransaction` in `read.rs`. - `DbWrite` is implemented for both `SharedStore` and `InMemoryTransaction` in `write.rs`. - The implementations for `InMemoryTransaction` are just delegating calls to the `SharedStore` implementations, i.e. super boilerplate. It uses a simple, naive optimistic concurrency check for concurrent transactions. Also implements `DbRead` and `DbWrite`. - `SharedStore` now implements `Transactable`, giving it `begin_transaction()` capabilities. ## Testing Information ## Checklist: - [x] I have performed a self-review of my code - [x] My changes generate no new warnings - [x] New and existing unit tests pass locally with my changes - [x] Any dependent changes have been merged and published in downstream modules
